race.comment: CATWALK ICON (5) was unplaced on debut then last start finished second over 1200m at Ballarat. Will be better for those outings and has the ability to take care of this field. DONATO (3) made an encouraging debut last time out, finishing a nose from the winner in second over 1100m at Tatura. Can get off the mark this time. CHICAGO BLUES (2) didn't do a lot on debut, when fifth, beaten 6 lengths, but comes into this with a couple of jumpout wins under his belt so an improved effort looks assured. HEGELY (8) is a two-start maiden who returned last time and finished fourth at Bendigo over 1000m, beaten 1.3 lengths. Bold showing expected with added fitness this time.
